<item>
            <title>[AMQ-1813] shutdownOnMasterFailure=&quot;true&quot; is ignored when broker starting</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-1813</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If slave broker cannot connect to master when slave broker starting, slave broker doesn&apos;t stop starting and starts all connectors&lt;br/&gt;
I think it&apos;s a bad behavior. It must shutdown when shutdownOnMasterFailure=&quot;true&quot; &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12482676">AMQ-1813</key>
            <summary>shutdownOnMasterFailure=&quot;true&quot; is ignored when broker starting</summary>
