                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12939932" author="yinghe0101" created="Tue, 15 Jul 2008 15:19:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;using tcp://master:61616 for masterConnectorURI and shutdownOnMasterFailure=&quot;true&quot; , I got the same result.  I think this needs to be fixed too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but using failover://(tcp://master:61616)?maxReconnectAttempts=3 as the masterConnectorURI , after 3 failed attemp, it will shut down the slave. so shutdownOnMasterFailure is not ignored in the failover protocol case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12939918" author="tsigelnik" created="Tue, 15 Jul 2008 15:47:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;2ying &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Your logic behaviour is result of race condition. Broker is already started when limit of maxReconnectAttempts=3 is exceeded&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12941602" author="rajdavies" created="Fri, 11 Sep 2009 18:49:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed by SVN revision 813980&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
